1. Once upon a time there were two people. [1]\
2. One of them was an expert laundryman. The other was an expert potter.\
3. One day, when they were comparing their wealth, [the potter thought] he didn\'92t earn as much as the laundryman, money-wise.[2]\
4. This potter thought that the laundryman was trying to ruin him.\
5. [So] he got an idea about a certain jet-black elephant that the local prince [3] had.\
6. The master potter knew in his heart that if the laundryman were to wash that elephant [4] and it didn\'92t turn white, he [the laundryman] would lose his livelihood, so he went [to the prince] and said:\
7. \'93My lord, O prince, if you would only wash the elephant white, when people would see it they\'92d say, "This is amazing!"\
8. So then the Prince said, \'93Who is there who can wash this elephant of mine white?\'94\
9. When he asked this, the potter said, \'93A certain expert laundryman can wash it white.\
10. \'93In fact he has a lot of money, more than me, more than me the master potter!\
11 \'93If you summon that fellow [5] and make him wash it, I believe it will really turn white,\'94 he said.\
12. When he said this, the lord prince said, \'93M\'fbl\'f2, go and summon here that master laundryman!\'94\
13. Then when he had been summoned and came, he [the laundryman] said, \'93My method of washing is that I must have a great big pot made, a huge basin 
