14. When he said this, the prince said to the potter, \'93O potter, you call your assistant(s) and make that pot!\'94\
15. So [they] made the pot and carried it [in] [7], and they took the elephant\'92s foot and put it in, and it shattered.\
16. After [the elephant] broke it once, broke it twice, broke it three times, the lord prince said, \'93Since you first thought you would ruin another person, now you have been ruined [yourself].\
17. \'93Do not earn your living as a potter anymore!\
18. \'93As for the laundryman, earn your living well by washing!\'94 he said.\
19. That\'92s the end.\
